{"lemma": "قَرارٌ", "slug": "قَرارٌ", "root": "ق.ر.ر", "root_slug": "ق-ر-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ق-ر-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "قَرار", "root": "قرر", "pos": "N", "occurrence_count": 9}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["noun"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 15}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n35350"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%8E%D8%B1%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}}, "translations": {"en": "settledness", "fa": "ثبات", "ur": "قرار", "tr": "karar", "id": "ketenangan", "bn": "স্থিরতা", "es": "estabilidad", "fr": "stabilité", "de": "Beständigkeit", "ru": "устойчивость", "zh": "安定"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "verbal noun of قَرَّ (qarra, “to be established, settled”) (form I)", "tags": ["form-of", "noun-from-verb"]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "decision", "examples": [{"text": "يَنْسُبُ ٱلاِقْتِصَادِيُّونَ ٱلرُّكُودَ إِلَى سِلْسِلَةٍ مِنَ ٱلْقَرَارَاتِ وَٱلسِيَاسَاتِ ٱلْمَالِيَّةِ غَيْرِ ٱلْمَحْظُوظَةِ.", "english": "Economists ascribe the recession to a series of unfortunate financial decisions and policies."}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "fixed residence, domicile"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "secure dwelling"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "stability"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "steadiness"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "perseverance"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "rest, quietude"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "patience"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "assurance, promise, agreement"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "security"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "truth"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "consent"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "deepest spot, bottom, low plain", "examples": [{"text": "Souad al-Sabah\nيَا لَهُمْ، وَاللُّؤْلُؤُ الْمَكْنُونُ فِي جَوْفِ الْبِحَارِ / لَمْ يَزَلْ يَسْأَلُ عَنْهُمْ كُلَّ لَيْلٍ وَنَهَارِ\nلَمْ يَزَلْ فِي شُعَبِ الْمَرْجَانِ حَيًّا وَدَفِينًا / فِي قَرَارٍ لَمْ تَطَأْهُ قَدَمٌ مُنْذُ سِنِينَ\nyā lahum, walluʔluʔ al-maknūnu fī jawfi l-biḥār / lam yazal yasʔalu ʕanhum kulla laylin wanahār\nlam yazal fī šuʕabi l-marjāni ḥayyan wadafīn / fī qarārin lam taṭaʔhu qadamun munḏu sinīn\nTo them, and the pearls located in the depths of the seas / still asking for them every night and day", "english": "Still in the reefs alive and buried / in a place no foot had touched for years"}]}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "pool"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/qa.raːr/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n35350", "headword_ar": "قَرَارٌ", "root": "qr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ": see 1, first signification. ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A state of settledness, fixedness, stability, establishment, quiet, stillness, rest, permanence,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "continuance;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb, TA;) and so ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~N", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in the Kur, ii. 34, and vii. 23: (Bd, TA:) or in these two instances the latter is a n. of place. (Bd.) [Hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "daAru AlqaraAri", "text_ar": "دَارُ القَرَارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[Kur, xl. 42,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The abode of stability; the permanent abode;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "i. e.,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the world to come."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "dwr", "text_ar": "دور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; &c.)       -A2-  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a time, of settledness, fixedness, stability, establishment, quiet, stillness, rest, permanence,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "continuance; a restingplace;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~N", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqar~N", "text_ar": "مَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qur~N", "text_ar": "قُرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, M, K.) Exs."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAra AlA^amoru A_ilaY qaraArihi", "text_ar": "صَارَ الاَمْرُ اـِلَى قَرَارِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~ihi", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرِّهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The thing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "affair, came to its place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "time, of settledness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or the meaning may be,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to its state of settledness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; the explanation is]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "came to its end, and became settle, fixed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c. (M, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "lahaA", "text_ar": "لَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAl$~amosu tajoriY limusotaqar~K", "text_ar": "وَالشَّمْسُ تَجْرِى لِمُسْتَقَرٍّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[Kur, xxxvi. 38,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And the sun runneth to a place, and time, beyond which it doth not pass:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to a term appointed for it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to a determined limit, where its revolution ends;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "likened to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mstqr~", "text_ar": "مستقرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of a traveller, when he ends his journey: or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the middle of the sky;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for it there seems to pause: or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to its state of settledness,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "according to a special path:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to its appointed end in one of the different places of rising and setting which it has on different days:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the end of its course, in the desolate part of the world:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and accord. to other readings,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA musotaqar~a lahaA", "text_ar": "لَا مُسْتَقَرَّ لَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA musotaqar~N lahaA", "text_ar": "لَا مُسْتَقَرٌّ لَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it has no rest;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for it is always in motion. (Bd.) And ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "likul~i nabaA_K musotaqar~N", "text_ar": "لِكُلِّ نَبَاـٍ مُسْتَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[Kur, vi. 66,]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "To every prophecy is a term"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[for its fulfilment], which ye shall see in the present world and in the world to come. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alr~aHimi", "text_ar": "الرَّحِمِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqar~u", "text_ar": "مَقَرُّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The extreme part of the womb; the resting-place"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the fœtus therein."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K.) It is said in the Kur, [vi. 98,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wamusotawodaEN", "text_ar": "وَمُسْتَوْدَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famusotaqar~N", "text_ar": "فَمُسْتَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "And"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "ye have"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a resting-place in the womb, and a depository"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the spermatic sources"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the back:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but some read"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "wamusotawodaEN", "text_ar": "وَمُسْتَوْدَعٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "famusotaqir~N", "text_ar": "فَمُسْتَقِرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[there is]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is yet remaining in the womb,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as is established in the present world, in existence, and such as is deposited in the back, not yet created:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "there is of you"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as remains among the living, and such as is deposited in the earth"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "among the dead"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (M, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as hath been born and hath appeared upon the earth, and such as is in the womb:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, TA:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "such as yet remains in the back, and such as is deposited in the womb."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A@lomuqad~asapa", "text_ar": "ا@لْمُقَدَّسَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^a*okaraniY A@lomaqaAr~a", "text_ar": "اَذْكَرَنِى ا@لْمَقَارَّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it, reminded me of the consecrated places of abode:"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqaAr~u", "text_ar": "مَقَارُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is pl. of ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maqar~N", "text_ar": "مَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) And one says, on the occasion of a calamity befalling, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAbato biqur~K", "text_ar": "صَابَتْ بِقُرٍّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Z, M, *) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaEato biqur~K", "text_ar": "وَقَعَتْ بِقُرٍّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(the calamity,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Al$~id~apu", "text_ar": "الشِّدَّةُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fell"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in its"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaraAr", "text_ar": "قَرَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "settled"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fixed place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in the place where it should remain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] (S, K:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the thing came to its"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaraAr", "text_ar": "قَرَار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it fell in its place:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Z:) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it fell where it ought:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Th:) and sometimes they said ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaEato biqur~ihaA", "text_ar": "وَقَعَتْ بِقُرِّهَا", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it fell in its settled"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fixed place,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.]: (S:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaEa AlA^amoru", "text_ar": "وَقَعَ الاَمْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biqur~ihi", "text_ar": "بِقُرِّهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", i. e. ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bimusotaqar~ihi", "text_ar": "بِمُسْتَقَرِّهِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the thing fell in the place where it did,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "should, rest,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "remain"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (As:) and one says to a man who seeks blood-revenge, when he meets the slayer of his relation, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waqaEota biqur~ika", "text_ar": "وَقَعْتَ بِقُرِّكَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "thy heart has met that which it looked for."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laqado waqaEotu biqur~ika", "text_ar": "لَقَدْ وَقَعْتُ بِقُرِّكَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biquHaAHi qur~ika", "text_ar": "بِقُحَاحِ قُرِّكَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", also means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I have become acquainted with all that thou knowest, nothing thereof being hidden from me."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Ibn-Buzurj, in TA, art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qH", "text_ar": "قح"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) One says also, [in threatening another,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laA^ulojivan~aka A_ilaY qur~i qaraArika", "text_ar": "لَاُلْجِثَنَّكَ اـِلَى قُرِّ قَرَارِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; a prov., meaning,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlY A^aSolika wajahodika", "text_ar": "الى اَصْلِكَ وَجَهْدِكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will assuredly impel thee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "drive thee, against thy will, to the utmost point to which thou canst go,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "be brought"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "reduced;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "constrain thee to do thine utmost"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (JK. [Or the meaning is,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I will assuredly impel thee,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "drive thee, against thy will, to the place that thou deservest:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to the place where thou shalt remain:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to thy grave:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "to thy worst and lowest state"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "condition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "see Freytag's Arab. Prov. ii. 450.]) ―         -b2-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A region,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place, of fixed abode; i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mina", "text_ar": "مِنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~N", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlA^aroDi", "text_ar": "الاَرْضِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (S:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a region, district,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "tract, of cities, towns,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "villages, and of cultivated land;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "syn."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaDarN", "text_ar": "حَضَرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (TA.) Hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aholu AlqaraAri", "text_ar": "اَهْلُ القَرَارِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The people residing in such a region"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaraAriY~N", "text_ar": "قَرَارِىٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", q. v. (TA.) [Hence,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almuloki wagayorihi", "text_ar": "المُلْكِ وَغَيْرِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "musotaqar~u", "text_ar": "مُسْتَقَرُّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The seat of regal power, &c."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] ―         -b3-"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "I. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maA qar~a fiyhi", "text_ar": "مَا قَرَّ فِيهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (as in a copy of the M,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA qur~a fyh", "text_ar": "ما قُرَّ فيه"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (as in copies of the K,) i. e.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mA qr~ fyh AlmA'", "text_ar": "ما قرّ فيه الماء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA, written without any syll. signs,) [app. meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A place in which water has remained,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "been poured"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as also ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaraArapN", "text_ar": "قَرَارَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, K:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a depressed piece of ground;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also the latter word: (M, K:) or the latter is applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "any depressed piece of ground into which water pours and where it remains;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and such ground is fertile, if the soil be soft: (AHn, M:) and to"}, {"kind":